HEADWORD: Hemiprotein
<hw>Hem`i*pro"te*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hemi-</ets> + <ets>protein</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>An insoluble, proteid substance, described by
Sch⟦uum⟧tzenberger, formed when albumin is heated for some time with
dilute sulphuric acid. It is apparently identical with antialbumid and
dyspeptone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

